---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../components/CodeBlock.astro';
import HealthTable from '../components/HealthTable.astro';
import ServiceCard from '../components/ServiceCard.astro';
import { services } from '../data/services';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Quickstart Guide & Modular Architecture"
  description="Follow our simple 3-step setup to launch your personal home server from scratch using Docker Compose."
>
  <div class="space-y-12">
    <!-- Intro Banner -->
    <section class="glass p-8 border border-accent/40 bg-gradient-to-br from-bg-surface via-bg-surface to-accent/5">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-0">⚡ Easiest Way to Begin</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
        You don't need to be a Linux system administrator to get started. Our interactive launcher handles folder structure creation, permission setups, and container orchestration automatically.
      </p>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 font-sans not-prose">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-bg border border-border">
          <span class="text-xs font-mono text-accent font-bold">STEP 01</span>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-text text-base mt-1">Bootstrap Host</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-1">Run our single script to install Docker and create `/srv` folders.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-bg border border-border">
          <span class="text-xs font-mono text-accent font-bold">STEP 02</span>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-text text-base mt-1">Interactive Menu</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-1">Run `bash scripts/launch.sh` and pick your stack from menu options 1–6.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-bg border border-border">
          <span class="text-xs font-mono text-accent font-bold">STEP 03</span>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-text text-base mt-1">Open Browser</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-1">Access your services at `http://YOUR_IP:PORT` instantly!</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Step 1 Command -->
    <section>
      <h2>1. Host Bootstrap (Ubuntu / Debian)</h2>
      <p>
        If you have a fresh installation of Ubuntu 22.04/24.04 or Debian 12, run this single command to install the official Docker Engine, Compose V2 plugin, and prepare storage directories under `/srv`:
      </p>
      <CodeBlock
        title="bash — Host Installation Script"
        code={`sudo bash <(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Zamiul-rashid/Homelabbing/main/quickstart/scripts/bootstrap.sh)`}
      />
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-yellow-950/20 border border-warning/30 text-xs text-warning not-prose">
        <strong>Important:</strong> After running `bootstrap.sh`, log out of your SSH session and log back in so your user's `docker` group membership takes effect!
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Step 2 Command -->
    <section>
      <h2>2. Clone and Launch</h2>
      <p>
        Clone the repository and run our interactive launcher. It will check if your `quickstart/.env` exists, open it for editing if needed, and let you select from our 6 numbered options:
      </p>
      <CodeBlock
        title="bash — Interactive Menu Launcher"
        code={`git clone https://github.com/Zamiul-rashid/Homelabbing.git\ncd Homelabbing/quickstart\nbash scripts/launch.sh`}
      />
      
      <div class="terminal-window not-prose border border-border my-6">
        <div class="terminal-titlebar">
          <span class="text-xs font-mono text-text-muted">scripts/launch.sh menu output</span>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 bg-terminal-bg font-mono text-xs text-terminal-text space-y-1">
          <p class="text-accent font-bold">==========================================================================</p>
          <p class="font-bold">  Pick a starting point to launch:</p>
          <p class="text-accent font-bold">==========================================================================</p>
          <p>  1) Jellyfin (simplest start — just a media player)</p>
          <p>  2) + Download automation (*arr stack)</p>
          <p>  3) + Music server (Navidrome)</p>
          <p>  4) + Photo backup (Immich)</p>
          <p>  5) + Cloud storage (Nextcloud)</p>
          <p>  6) Everything (full stack)</p>
          <p class="text-accent font-bold">==========================================================================</p>
          <p class="pt-2">Enter choice [1-6]: <span class="text-accent animate-pulse">_</span></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Explore Services Directory -->
    <section>
      <h2>3. Explore the Individual Stacks</h2>
      <p>
        Want to inspect the Docker Compose definitions or read specific onboarding guides for a particular service? Click any card below to open its dedicated walkthrough:
      </p>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 not-prose my-8">
        {services.map((s) => (
          <ServiceCard service={s} />
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Health table -->
    <section>
      <h2>4. Health Checking Across All Ports</h2>
      <p>
        To verify that all containers are running cleanly without error loops or broken permissions, run `bash scripts/check-health.sh` at any time:
      </p>
      <HealthTable />
    </section>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
